            "weighting": "<dd>35%</dd>",
            "due_date": "<dd><p> 25/09/2026 4:00 pm</p></dd>",
            "learning_objectives": "L01, L02, L03",
            "mode": "Product/ Artefact/ Multimedia",
            "category": "Presentation, Poster",
            "task_description": "<div class=\"collapsible collapsible--text\">\n<p>Students will be required to design an infographic on an issue relating to the first 7 weeks of course content on climate economics. Students must also record a 3–4-minute presentation on the infographic explaining the purpose and analysis provided by the infographic. It is required that students are physically and clearly visible in the recording. We recommend using Zoom or Teams to record your infographic presentation. </p>\n<p>Please See Blackboard for specific question, details, and criteria.</p>\n<button class=\"collapsible__toggle\">\n<span class=\"collapsible__open link--icon icon--standard--arrow-down-1\">Read full task description</span>\n<span class=\"collapsible__close link--icon icon--standard--arrow-up-1\">Hide full task description</span>\n</button>\n</div>",
            "submission_guidelines": "<p>Submit via Turnitin, Blackboard by the due date/time specified.</p>",
            "deferral_or_extension": "<p>You may be able to <a href=\"https://my.uq.edu.au/information-and-services/manage-my-program/exams-and-assessment/applying-assessment-extension\">apply for an extension</a>.</p>",
            "late_submission": "<p>A <a href=\"https://policies.uq.edu.au/document/view-current.php?id=184\">penalty</a> of 10% of the maximum possible mark will be deducted per 24 hours from time submission is due for up to 7 days. After 7 days, you will receive a mark of 0.</p>",
            "additional_info": "<p>You may be able to <a href=\"https://my.uq.edu.au/information-and-services/manage-my-program/exams-and-assessment/applying-assessment-extension\">apply for an extension</a>.</p>"
        },
        {
            "assessment_detail_section_id": "assessment-detail-2",
            "assessment_title": "Climate Policy Brief (maximum 1 page)",
            "special_indicators": [],
            "weighting": "<dd>35%</dd>",
            "due_date": "<dd><p> 30/10/2026 4:00 pm</p></dd>",
            "learning_objectives": "L02, L03, L04",
            "mode": "Written",
            "category": "Project",
            "task_description": "<div class=\"collapsible collapsible--text\">\n<p>As part of the policy brief, students are expected to conduct through research on the selected policy issue, analyse the economic aspects of the policy issue and use economic graphs to illustrate key relationships, trends or comparisons.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Page Limit: 1 page (single-sided).</li>\n<li>A maximum two graphs, tables, or other illustrations in total can be provided on a second page.</li>\n<li>Margin Size: Minimum of a 1.5cm margins on all sides. Smaller margins will result in a penalty.</li>\n<li>Font Size: Use a legible font size 11-point such as Times New Roman, Calibri or Arial.</li>\n<li>Line Spacing: Minimum single line spacing</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Please See Blackboard for specific question, details, and criteria.</p>\n<button class=\"collapsible__toggle\">\n<span class=\"collapsible__open link--icon icon--standard--arrow-down-1\">Read full task description</span>\n<span class=\"collapsible__close link--icon icon--standard--arrow-up-1\">Hide full task description</span>\n</button>\n</div>",
            "submission_guidelines": "<p>Submit via Turnitin, Blackboard by the due date/time specified.</p>",
